description: Brian Pulido's Celtic vixen is born! Wexford, Ireland, 999 AD. Samhain. Though Colleen MacGrath (aka Belladonna) has laid dormant for years, Morrigan the Celtic goddess forces Colleen to rise and again claim vengeance for all the Celtic people! A druid has resurrected the dead Vikings who murdered Colleen's family and has set them upon the town. Now it is up to Belladonna to stop the Undead horde. Will Belladonna succeed? Or will the sheer numbers finally put her to rest forever? Originally presented in Belladonna Convention Special & Belladonna #0.

Wexford Ireland, 950 AD. Colleen MacGrath's wedding to Donovan was to unite two powerful Irish families in bliss. Instead, all their hopes and dreams were laid to waste by marauding Vikings. Now a year later, on Samhain, Morrigan the Celtic goddess forces Colleen to rise and claim vengeance as Belladonna! Belladonna is a tale steeped in passion, violence and darkness as only Boundless Comics can bring you. Originally presented in Belladonna #1.

Belladonna begins to hunt down those responsible for her death, and discovers that coming back to life may have given her other powers! However, coming back from the dead brings it's own burdens, problems that Belladonna must face before the Vikings kill her again. With stellar art by Clint Hilinski and stunning colors by Nimbus Studios, Belladonna will appeal to the legions of Boundless Comics bad girl fans. Originally presented in Belladonna #2.

Belladonna has returned from the dead to strike down those who threaten Wexford and to hunt for the Vikings who killed her love. Now her quest for vengeance leads her into an enslaved town overrun with Viking tormentors. With a huge number of foes, she must call on her animal friends to help lead the assault! Originally presented in Belladonna #3.

description:
Dark Horse Comics is proud to present a series of digital sampler comics, Builds Characters. Each sampler will focus on a single creator and excerpt variety of their past and upcoming works with Dark Horse.

Enjoy this free sampling from Eisner Awardwinning artist Eric Powell, featuring a choice selection of The Goon, as well as excerpts from Chimichanga and Billy the Kid's Old Timey Oddities!

With the four realms of power - Myst, Neverland, Oz, and Wonderland - at Sela Mather's fingertips, life as the protector of the Earth has never been more work. However, when Sela is put in charge of a group of young, powerful Highborns, she finds that defending the realms from the threat of otherworldly forces may be the least of her worries.

As the first year of Arcane Acre draws to a close, its students are targeted by the malevolent spirit from the nightmarish realm of Wonderland... but little do they know, the spirit's connection to one of their own might prove to be their downfall.

Collects Grimm Fairy Tales #107 - 112.
name: Volume Two

description:
From the mind of legendary creator Grant Morrison. Bheeshma, the last super-warrior from an earlier age joins the battle at last unleashing terror from the skies. "Grandfather Bheeshma is the Big Man. Bheeshma the Terrible. The SUPREME Superwarrior of his Age, Indestructible Bheeshma. He's Obi Wan Kenobi and Arnold rolled into one but his time is coming to an end and perhaps he can feel the chill. No matter, it is said that Bheeshma will die only when he wants to..." -Grant Morrison

And stick around as Clark Kents expos A Day in our Lives hits the Daily Planet!

What happens to a man whose life, family and purpose has left him behind...and how will he create new purpose once forced to renew his fight?

Suske and Wiske are travelling with Lies when their car breaks down. They walk to the nearest house where there's still light. The friendly man invites them in to spend the night. In the morning Suske and Wiske discover they have arrived at a special place: they're having breakfast with several Zwarte Pieten! It promises to become a very exciting day for our two little friends.

description:
People who live in chaos can never escape it, and the Punisher is no exception. When trying to escape his own personal war he is drawn into another. In a small town in Missouri the firefight starts and Frank is pulled right into it, again our country is at the top. As a Retired U.S. Army General thinks the world should be purified of the filth.

Frank wants to escape this war, but he cannot. And he makes it obvious he is angry that his vacation was interrupted.
name: El Diablo vino de Kansas

description: When a crazed religious nut The Rev arms his people with guns, Frank Castle takes his own arms. While working with a cop who has a great disdain for the Church of The Saved, he goes in undercover as a man who has a great hate for his country and its people. Will what he finds will give him the edge to bring the Rev and the Church of the Saved to the ground.
name: El Reverendo

description: While still undercover within the Revs church he finds that keeping his cover secret is just as easy as petting a porcupine. He must train these fanatics how to use the weapons the Rev procured, but will he do it knowing full well that he is leading them to their deaths. A War is coming for the church, but will Frank stop it or will the Revs healing touch be too much for him to overcome. In the end people will die... But will one of the dead be the Punisher?
name: Ministro de la muerte

description:
MAKE WAY FOR THE TANK GIRL OF THE NEW MILLENIUM! After a break of 20 years, artist extraordinaire Jamie Hewlett (GORILLAZ) is leaping back on the Tank Girl wagon, re-teaming with series co-creator Alan Martin to bring you a whole new take on the foul-mouthed, gun toting, swill-swigging hellion! Featuring riotous 100% original content from Hewlett & Martin along with contributions from a host of series stalwarts and newcomers, get your head down, put your hands over your private parts, and prepare for a chaotic collection of strips, pin-ups, and random carnage!

Note: The digital edition (11/4/2015) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: HC

description: The once peaceful city of Park Falls has been tainted by a series of missing persons and gruesome murders. Town crazy Cynthia Ford comes forward to speak with retired police detective Derrick Peters one January afternoon with information about the strange happenings, claiming that they're connected. But does she hold the key to unlocking the mystery, or has she gone completely insane? To Derrick's disbelief she utters one word: Zombies. The answers await Derrick, federal scientist Dr. Daniel Howe, attack survivor Sandra LaFayette, and the rest of the city, but will they lead to salvation or the end of life as we know it? Investigate the mystery and dive into the horror of the critically acclaimed zombie noir series, Awakening, now collected in one giant volume, including a short story, production extras, guest pin-ups, and more.
name: TPB

description:
His suit's torn to shreds, his city's dying, and he's been up to his neck in Inque and cyborgs since he got thrown into this hellish future! But he's done being told he's not Batman, and he's taking the fight to the moon for humanity's final showdown with Brother Eye! This is it-the conclusion to the struggle started way back in FUTURES END #0!

description: The Punisher infiltrates the home of the leader of the "ninja camp" trying to find out where Iris Green is. Instead he finds files on a ton of dirt bags and a U.S. Congressman. The Punisher torches the house and goes after the leader of the camp of his two instructors who are trying to kill everyone in the camp to keep their secrets from being exposed. Includes material from The Punisher Vol. 2 #23 and The Punisher War Journal Vol. 1 #3.
name: Capturar la bandera

description: Punisher takes a break from hunting Iris Green and goes to Japan after being invited by a world renowned martial arts master Hatsu Yakamoto. He heads to the village where the martial artist is suppose to live and ends up being attacked by a member of a group called the eternal sun. Later on Frank and the martial arts master and his students get into a fight with the eternal sun defeating them. Castle and Yakamoto and his students decide to go after and end the eternal sun. Includes material from The Punisher Vol. 2 #24 and The Punisher War Journal Vol. 1 #4.
name: La Tierra del sol eterno
